---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Section 75 Claim Helper collects, uses, and protects your personal data."
>
  <article class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">

    <h1>Privacy policy</h1>

    <p>
      This policy explains what personal data this website collects, why, how long it is kept, and what rights you have over it. It covers only data processed by or on behalf of this site. It does not cover third-party websites that this site links to.
    </p>

    <p>
      This site is operated as an information service. We do not handle Section 75 claims on your behalf or correspond with banks in your name.
    </p>

    <h2>What data we collect and why</h2>

    <h3>Contact form</h3>

    <p>
      When you submit a message via the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>, we receive your name, email address, and the content of your message. This is processed via Formspree, a third-party form service, and forwarded to our email inbox. We use it solely to respond to your enquiry. We do not add contact form submissions to any mailing list.
    </p>

    <h3>Purchases</h3>

    <p>
      If you buy the claim pack, payment is processed by Stripe. You are directed to Stripe's checkout to complete your purchase. We do not receive, process, or store your card number or any other payment card details at any point. Stripe collects and processes your billing name, email address, and payment details directly, under their own privacy policy.
    </p>

    <p>
      After a successful purchase, Stripe or the associated delivery service sends a download email to the address you provided at checkout. We retain a record of the transaction (date, amount, email address) for accounting purposes.
    </p>

    <h3>Analytics and cookies</h3>

    <p>
      This site does not currently use analytics scripts or set tracking cookies. No third-party advertising or profiling technology is active on these pages.
    </p>

    <p>
      When you interact with Formspree (contact form) or Stripe (checkout), those services may set their own cookies on their own domains. Those interactions are governed by Formspree's and Stripe's respective privacy policies, not this one.
    </p>

    <h2>How long we keep your data</h2>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Contact form messages:</strong> retained only as long as needed to handle your enquiry, then deleted from our inbox.</li>
      <li><strong>Purchase records:</strong> we retain basic transaction records (date, amount, email address) for six years, as required for UK tax and accounting purposes. Full payment data is held by Stripe under their own retention policy.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Who we share data with</h2>

    <p>
      We share your data only with the third-party processors necessary to operate this site:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Formspree</strong> — processes contact form submissions. Their privacy policy is at <a href="https://formspree.io/legal/privacy-policy">formspree.io/legal/privacy-policy</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Stripe</strong> — processes payments. Their privacy policy is at <a href="https://stripe.com/gb/privacy">stripe.com/gb/privacy</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with any other party, and we do not use it for marketing purposes.
    </p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>

    <p>
      Under UK GDPR, you have the right to:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>request a copy of any personal data we hold about you;</li>
      <li>ask us to correct inaccurate data;</li>
      <li>ask us to delete data we hold, subject to our legal obligations (such as the six-year accounting retention period for purchase records);</li>
      <li>object to processing or ask us to restrict it.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      To exercise any of these rights, contact us via the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>. We will respond within 30 days.
    </p>

    <p>
      If you are unhappy with how we have handled your data, you have the right to complain to the Information Commissioner's Office at <a href="https://ico.org.uk">ico.org.uk</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>

    <p>
      If we make material changes to this policy, we will update this page. The date below reflects when the policy was last revised.
    </p>

    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Last updated: 1 May 2026</p>

  </article>
</BaseLayout>
